  "title": "Monitoring des capacités d'échanges aux frontières françaises de la région Italie Nord",
  "description": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.5pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style='font-size:9.5pt;font-family:\"Segoe UI\",sans-serif;\nmso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";color:#1F497D;mso-fareast-language:\nFR'>« Monitoring Paquet Energie Propre 70% »</span></b><b><span style='font-size:9.5pt;font-family:\"Segoe UI\",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\n\"Times New Roman\";color:#585858;mso-fareast-language:FR'> </span></b><span style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:\"Segoe UI\",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\n\"Times New Roman\";color:#585858;mso-fareast-language:FR'><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.5pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style='font-size:9.5pt;font-family:\"Segoe UI\",sans-serif;\nmso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";color:#1F497D;mso-fareast-language:\nFR'>Le règlement européen de l’électricité, dans le cadre du Paquet Energie\nPropre adopté en 2019, exige des GRT d’être en mesure de monitorer la capacité\ndu réseau devant être mis à disposition des échanges transfrontaliers en\nintroduisant une cible ambitieuse de 70%. Selon la recommandation de l’ACER\n(Agency for the Cooperation of Energy Regulators), ce monitoring s’effectue,\nsur chaque pas de temps, à la maille des éléments critiques de réseaux qui sont\nfournis aux différents calculs de capacité pour les échanges aux frontières au\nsein de l’Union Européenne.</span><span style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:\n\"Segoe UI\",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";color:#585858;\nmso-fareast-language:FR'><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.5pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style='font-size:9.5pt;font-family:\"Segoe UI\",sans-serif;\nmso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";color:#1F497D;mso-fareast-language:\nFR'>Dans ce cadre, RTE et la CRE souhaitent mettre à disposition de tous, les\ndonnées de monitoring qui sont produites sur le sujet au niveau français.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.5pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style='font-size:9.5pt;font-family:\"Segoe UI\",sans-serif;\nmso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";color:#1F497D;mso-fareast-language:\nFR'>SWE, Europe du Centre Ouest (CORE/CWE)  et NIB sont les 3 régions de calcul de\ncapacité au sein de l’Union Européenne, auquel RTE participe (SWE pour la\nfrontière avec l’Espagne ; NIB pour Frontière avec l’Italie ; CWE\npour les frontières avec Allemagne et Belgique). Depuis le 9 juin 2022, CORE a remplacé la région CWE. On gardera le terme de CWE pour les données du 1er janvier 2022 au 8 juin 2022.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:7.5pt;line-height:normal\">\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.5pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style='font-size:9.5pt;font-family:\"Segoe UI\",sans-serif;\nmso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";color:#1F497D;mso-fareast-language:\nFR'>Pour les régions CWE/CORE et SWE, retrouvez les jeux de données ci-dessous\n:<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:7.5pt;line-height:normal\"><a href=\"https://odre.opendatasoft.com/explore/dataset/monitoring-capacites-echanges-core-2022/information/?disjunctive.maczt_superieure_a_70&amp;disjunctive.valeur_ajoutee_a_appliquer_le_cep_70\">Monitoring des capacités d'échanges aux frontières françaises de la région CORE/Europe du Centre-Ouest — Open Data Réseaux Énergies (ODRÉ) (opendatasoft.com)</a></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:7.5pt;line-height:normal\"><a href=\"https://odre.opendatasoft.com/explore/dataset/monitoring-capacites-echanges-cwe-2021-2022/information/?disjunctive.valeur_ajoutee_a_appliquer_le_cep_70&amp;disjunctive.maczt_superieure_a_70\">Monitoring des capacités d'échanges aux frontières françaises de la région CWE/Europe du Centre-Ouest — Open Data Réseaux Énergies (ODRÉ) (opendatasoft.com)</a><br></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:7.5pt;line-height:normal\"><a href=\"https://odre.opendatasoft.com/explore/dataset/monitoring-capacites-echanges-swe-2021-2022/information/?disjunctive.valeur_ajoutee_a_appliquer_le_cep_70&amp;disjunctive.maczt_superieure_a_70\">Monitoring des capacités d'échanges aux frontières françaises de la région Europe du Sud-Ouest — Open Data Réseaux Énergies (ODRÉ) (opendatasoft.com)</a><br></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:7.5pt;line-height:normal\"><span style='font-size: 9.5pt; font-family: \"Segoe UI\", sans-serif;'><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.5pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style='font-size:9.5pt;font-family:\"Segoe UI\",sans-serif;\nmso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";color:#1F497D;mso-fareast-language:\nFR'>La description des frontières est en pièce jointe.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.5pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style='font-size:9.5pt;font-family:\"Segoe UI\",sans-serif;\nmso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";color:#1F497D;mso-fareast-language:\nFR'>Les pas de temps correspondant à des erreurs du calcul de capacité qui ne\npermettent pas de réaliser correctement l’évaluation du CEP 70% ou bien à des\nerreurs de reporting, ont été rajoutés aux jeux de données de 2022. Ils sont\nreprésentés par le terme « Process Fail during TTC Calculation » dans la\ncolonne « Nom de la CNEC ».<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.5pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style='font-size:9.5pt;font-family:\"Segoe UI\",sans-serif;\nmso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";color:#1F497D;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;\nmso-fareast-language:FR'>« Monitoring Clean Energy Package 70% »</span></b><b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style='font-size:9.5pt;font-family:\"Segoe UI\",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\n\"Times New Roman\";color:#585858;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:\nFR'> </span></b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:\"Segoe UI\",sans-serif;\nmso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";color:#585858;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;\nmso-fareast-language:FR'><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.5pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style='font-size:9.5pt;font-family:\"Segoe UI\",sans-serif;\nmso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";color:#1F497D;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;\nmso-fareast-language:FR'>The european electricity regulation introduces in\n2019, a minimum threshold of 70% of the capacity to be made available for\ncross-border trade. In the frame of this regulation, TSOs have to be able to\nmonitor this network capacity. According to ACER (Agency for the Cooperation of\nEnergy Regulators) recommendation, this monitoring takes place, on each\nTimestamp, on the critical network element provided by TSOs to the capacity\ncalculation project at European Union level.</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:\"Segoe UI\",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\n\"Times New Roman\";color:#585858;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:\nFR'><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.5pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style='font-size:9.5pt;font-family:\"Segoe UI\",sans-serif;\nmso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";color:#1F497D;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;\nmso-fareast-language:FR'>Within this framework, RTE and CRE (Commission de\nRégulation de l’Energie) would like to share, in Opendata, the dataset produced\non the subject on French level.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:7.5pt;line-height:normal\">\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.5pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style='font-size:9.5pt;font-family:\n\"Segoe UI\",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";color:#1F497D;\nmso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:FR'>The time steps corresponding\nto errors in the capacity calculation that do not allow the evaluation of the\n70% CEP to be carried out correctly, or to errors in the monitoring tool used\nby RTE, have been added to the 2022 data sets. They are represented by the term\n\"</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style='font-size:9.5pt;font-family:\"Segoe UI\",sans-serif;\nmso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";color:#1F497D;mso-fareast-language:\nFR'> </span><span style='font-size:9.5pt;font-family:\"Segoe UI\",sans-serif;\nmso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";color:#1F497D;mso-fareast-language:\nFR'>Process Fail during TTC </span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style='font-size:9.5pt;\nfont-family:\"Segoe UI\",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\ncolor:#1F497D;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:FR'>\" in the\ncolumn \"Name of the CNEC\".<o:p></o:p></span></p>",
